# Tool Registration Rules

These three files must stay in sync. Every tool needs entries in ALL THREE:

1. **platform_registry.py** — Tool schema (name, description, parameters)
2. **dynamic_tool_registry.py** — Tool availability rules (which users/tiers get access)
3. **tool_executor.py** — Dispatch mapping (tool_name → service method call)

## After Any Change
```bash
python scripts/verify_tools.py    # Checks consistency across all 3 files
```

## Adding a New Tool
```python
# 1. platform_registry.py
"my_tool": {
    "name": "my_tool",
    "description": "What it does",
    "inputSchema": {"type": "object", "properties": {...}, "required": [...]}
}

# 2. tool_executor.py — add dispatch case
elif tool_name == "my_tool":
    result = await self._execute_my_platform_tool(tool_name, arguments)

# 3. dynamic_tool_registry.py — add to appropriate platform tools list
```
